@E G do a bunch of Monday's from the archive. It's the easiest day, so less stressful, and you'll develop that crossword brain where you know to the go-to answers like AGAR/AGRA, ENO, and OREO, just to name a few. And you learn patterns to sniff out misdirects. 

Proper nouns and obscure clues are always gonna be a challenge unless your knowledge happens to overlap with that day's creator, but overall it does get easier once you get the hang of it. 

Rebus' suck though. I stand by my process of doing a word search on the column before I jump into all Thursdays, to figure out if there is one that day or not. I do these puzzles to relax and a rebus puzzle  that I don't know is a rebus puzzle does not aid in that effort! So I check first now.

